  "texts": [
    "Page 15 of 38 86",
    "Around 80% of rare diseases are related to genetic variations (Liu et al. 2019).",
    "Hence, the importance of diagnoses provided by genome sequencing.",
    "The advancements in Next Generation Sequencing (NGS) technology have led to the collection of vast amounts of data and provided rich information about individual genomes.",
    "The bottleneck in NGS lies in the analysis and interpretation of large-scale genome data and the identification of variants (Lucena-Perez et al. 2021)."
  ]
}